title: Independent candidate Mir Mumtaz Hussain wins PS- 3 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Independent candidate Mir Mumtaz Hussain Khan has won the Sindh Assembly election from PS-3, Jacobabad-III by securing 39,600 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Aurangzaib Pinhor of the Pakistan People’s Party Parliamentarian, who bagged votes 31587.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 42.02 %.
